observation: The 'Themes' page on the Oh My Zsh wiki provides instructions on how to change the theme. To change the zsh theme to 'agnoster', you need to set `ZSH_THEME="agnoster"` in your `~/.zshrc` file and then source it by running `source ~/.zshrc`. This information is found under the general theme instructions on the page.
